To produce the final most likely maps (neighborhood analysis) we looped through the different layers in the following order until an open (or woody savanna/forest) land class was found: current MODIS (2001 and 2010 land cover), the nested grids (from finer to coarser resolutions), ecoregion, climate-biome at the region level and finally biome worldwide. In most cases, over 95% of the most likely open land class and over 75% of the forest class assigned was found within the 10° grid (see Fig. S

 8

). Notable exceptions are deserts, montane grasslands, tundra or temperate grasslands where trees are unlikely to grow and thus have low restoration potential regardless of final forest cover (see “Data availability”).
